<HEADLINE>
FT  25 JAN 92 / Stringfellow liquidation
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By MICHAEL SKAPINKER
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
STRINGFELLOW Enterprises, owner of nightclubs in London and the US, last
night said it had gone into voluntary liquidation as a result of
difficulties at its three US venues, Michael Skapinker writes.
The company said its London nightclub, Stringfellows, would remain open.
Nightclubs in New York, Los Angeles and Miami have sought Chapter 11
protection under US bankruptcy laws. The company said it was unlikely that
they would be able to repay money owed to the London club, by which they had
been funded. The Miami club had closed and was up for sale.
The company said Mr Peter Stringfellow, the nightclub's founder, would
concentrate on his UK business and planned a second club in London.
