<HEADLINE>
FT  24 JAN 92 / International Company News: Scott Paper to cut 10% jobs
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By MARTIN DICKSON
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   NEW YORK
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
SCOTT PAPER, the world's largest manufacturer of toilet tissue, announced
plans to cut its workforce by around 10 per cent, or 3,800. It will also
take a Dollars 183m after-tax special charge in the fourth quarter, about
half of it due to the job cuts, which will push it into losses for the
period.
Scott, which faces ferocious competition in the US, attributed the cuts to
'the difficult economic environment and highly competitive market
conditions.' It estimated that fourth-quarter earnings, due to be announced
on January 30, would total around 35 cents a share excluding the special
charge, which would work through at about Dollars 2.49.
