customers are dealt with by TSB's Hill Samuel subsidiary which lost Pounds
419m last year.
Mr Charles Love, chief executive of TSB Bank Scotland, said it fared better
than the division as a whole because of the better economic climate in
Scotland, although that had worsened in the second half of the year. He said
costs rose by only 4.6 per cent.
