FT  24 JAN 92 / Observer: Greek to me
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
No surprise that ubiquitous Tony O'Reilly - top bean at Heinz, balked bidder
for Fairfax, rugby legend etc etc - should be spreading his ample self yet
thinner, this time as chairman of a new 'European advisory board' at Bankers
Trust.
However, also on the list of Bankers' luminous European experts is 'a
private investor with interests in shipping, real estate and insurance'.
That is Greek-born Chryss O'Reilly, the Goulandris shipping heiress, who
also happened to emerge last year as the second Mrs O'Reilly.
'What kind of question is that?', the bank's mouthpiece snapped when asked
why it sought her wisdom on European strategy. The multi-
millionairess had been invited on to the board in her own right in advance
of tying the knot with the gifted Irishman.
Yet according to one of her acquaintances, a fellow Greek, the expert
horsewoman never showed much interest in business before.
