<TEXT>
HOTELS and restaurants in the UK have responded to the recession by raising
standards while maintaining or even cutting prices, according to the editor
of the 1992 Michelin guide, which was published yesterday.
Mr Derek Brown said that the guide, in spite of the recession, had added
nine restaurants to its list of Michelin-starred establishments.
