three-star ranking. La Tante Claire in Chelsea; Harvey's in Wands-worth,
south London; Chez Nico in Westminster; Le Manoir aux Quat' Saisons near
Oxford; and L'Ortolan, near Reading kept their two stars. There were 36
one-star establishments.
Mr Brown said more restaurants had introduced fixed-price menus, many
offering a wider choice than previously.
